<div>
    <article class="columns small-12 medium-6 medium-offset-3">
        <p>Despite opposition from some locals that divided the small island community, the AUD$17million project&#x2014;the largest ever attempted on an inhabited island&#x2014;has been a boon for the island&#x2019;s biodiversity, says Ian Hutton, naturalist and curator of Lord Howe&#x2019;s excellent museum.</p>
<p>&#x201C;We didn&#x2019;t expect the woodhen population to increase so quickly,&#x201D; said Hutton, noting that numbers are thought to have tripled since the release of 230 individuals back onto the island in early 2020. But it&#x2019;s not the only species flourishing.</p>

</article> </div>


<div>
    <article class="columns small-12 medium-6 medium-offset-3">
            <blockquote>
                <p>While it may be some time yet before the Lord Howe Island Board is confident in declaring the island rodent-free, this is a glorious era to visit this New South Wales outpost.</p>
<p class="quotee"></p>            </blockquote>
    </article>
 </div>



<div>
    <article class="columns small-12 medium-6 medium-offset-3">
        <p>Over a Lord Howe Island Distilling Co. gin at lagoon-side bar, The Crooked Post, owner Tim Cruikshank pointed out a colony of noddy terns that only recently began nesting in the surrounding Norfolk pines. A raft of more subtle ecological changes have also been observed by locals including sixth-generation islander Anthony Riddle, a tour operator and co-founder of the local gin company.</p>
<p>&#x201C;I&#x2019;ve never seen so many butterflies,&#x201D; Riddle told me during a glass-bottom boat tour of the turtle hangouts in the island&#x2019;s lagoon. &#x201C;Some species I&#x2019;ve never seen on the island before.&#x201D;</p>

</article> </div>


<figure>

<div class="row expanded collapse small-up-1 "><img class="gallery " data-lazy-src="https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-Sooty-terns-nesting-at-Clear-Place-Point..1-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1920x1080.jpg" src="https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-Sooty-terns-nesting-at-Clear-Place-Point..1-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1920x1080.jpg" srcset="https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-Sooty-terns-nesting-at-Clear-Place-Point..1-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1920x1080.jpg 1920w, https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-Sooty-terns-nesting-at-Clear-Place-Point..1-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1180x664.jpg 1180w" sizes="(max-width: 3840) 100vw, 3840" alt="Two black and white birds."></div><div class="row expanded collapse small-up-1 medium-up-2 img-block-col-2 "><div class="column"><img class="gallery " data-lazy-src="https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-This-jewel-beetle-is-so-rare-it-hasn_t-been-scientifically-named-yet.-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1920x1080.jpg" src="https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-This-jewel-beetle-is-so-rare-it-hasn_t-been-scientifically-named-yet.-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1920x1080.jpg" srcset="https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-This-jewel-beetle-is-so-rare-it-hasn_t-been-scientifically-named-yet.-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1920x1080.jpg 1920w, https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-This-jewel-beetle-is-so-rare-it-hasn_t-been-scientifically-named-yet.-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1180x664.jpg 1180w" sizes="(max-width: 3840) 100vw, 3840" alt="A magnetic looking beetle."></div><div class="column"><img class="gallery " data-lazy-src="https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-White-tern-hanging-out-at-Lord-Howe_s-dive-centre.-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1920x1080.jpg" src="https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-White-tern-hanging-out-at-Lord-Howe_s-dive-centre.-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1920x1080.jpg" srcset="https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-White-tern-hanging-out-at-Lord-Howe_s-dive-centre.-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1920x1080.jpg 1920w, https://adventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Lord-Howe-Island-White-tern-hanging-out-at-Lord-Howe_s-dive-centre.-Image-credit-Sarah-Reid-1180x664.jpg 1180w" sizes="(max-width: 3840) 100vw, 3840" alt="A white tern on a rope."></div></div>
